This directory contains formal stability invariants that harden BELLA’s belief lifecycle against edge-case failure modes discovered during recursive stress testing.

These invariants do not redesign BELLA’s core mechanics. Instead, they clarify how verification events, falsifiability, and historical scope must behave to prevent false stabilization and irreversible belief locking.

Typical contents include:

Verification stability rules (e.g., A4, A4′)
Historical scope validation logic (e.g., A5)
Anchor qualification boundary conditions
Cascade and revalidation rules triggered by new conflicts

Goal:

Ensure that beliefs which stabilize into long-term anchors remain correctable, historically consistent, and resistant to self-sealing verification loops.
